# Wave 6 — /api/<slug> retirement.
#
# Astro's `redirects` map can't add a URL fragment to a redirect
# destination (`/#[slug]` is not an Astro route, so the build fails).
# Netlify reads this file at the edge and rewrites with `:splat`,
# preserving the path segment as the new anchor on `/`.
#
# Order matters — Netlify uses the first matching rule. The bare
# `/api` and `/components` index routes are also handled by Astro's
# `redirects` map (see `astro.config.mjs`); the wildcard rules below
# cover the per-slug case that Astro can't express.

/api/*         /#:splat   301!
/components/*  /#:splat   301!

# Wave 4 · 4.7 — `/foundations/*` and `/guides/<slug>` deep links
# fold into `/handbook` anchors. The handful of static cases live in
# `astro.config.mjs`; this catches everything else.
/foundations/*  /handbook  301
